President Joe Biden will host a trilateral leaders summit with Prime Minister Kishida Fumio of Japan and President Yoon Suk Yeol of the Republic of Korea at Camp David on August 18, 2023. The summit aims to strengthen the bonds of friendship and alliances between the United States and Japan, as well as the United States and the Republic of Korea. The leaders will discuss expanding trilateral cooperation in the Indo-Pacific region and addressing the threat posed by the DPRK. They will also focus on strengthening ties with ASEAN and the Pacific Islands. The summit will promote a rules-based international order, address global and regional security challenges, and bolster economic prosperity.